  <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">A subscription brand uses last-touch as its only model. The dashboard says Email drives 40% of revenue &mdash; the team reads this as &quot;Email is our hero channel&quot; and increases the email program budget two quarters in a row.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">Then they pause Paid Social in three matched geos for a month. Revenue in the holdout regions falls 22% below control. Recomputing with Linear attribution, Email's share drops to 18% and Paid Social's share rises from 12% to 31%. The Email flow was closing customers Paid Social had already brought to the site &mdash; not driving them. They cut the email program back, reallocate to Paid Social, and blended ROAS climbs because the budget is now upstream of the conversion, not piled on top of it.</p>
